                    <span>Bhagvad Gita is a Wonderful Poem in Indian Literature (Sanskrit language).  But given the fact that this language is no longer spoken (just like Latin), the contents of the great works such as Bhagvad Gita have to be  read in translated forms.<p>Sir Arnold's translation is in poetic form,  unlike most translations, which are mainly prose.<p>It makes for a concise  reading, without really missing the the essence.<p>The Gita is my Manager,  and I have personally benefitted immensely in dealing with main daily life  sitiuations both in family and work.  It has made a profound diference to  my decision making ability qand leadership qualities.<p>I sincerely hope  that every ambitious person takes time to read this and beenfit from the  relevant parts of the text.</span>
                  
